om.administration.extraction
Class StudentDetailsExtractor

java.lang.Object
  om.tnavigator.AbstractPersistenceDelegator
      om.administration.extraction.StudentDetailsExtractor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Extractor, GracefulFinalization
public class StudentDetailsExtractor
extends AbstractPersistenceDelegator
implements Extractor, GracefulFinalization

Handles the extraction of the students details from the underlying persistence mechanism in Openmark so that their details can be reused within another environment (at this time for testing if they have problems) Equally can be reused for other purposes in the future.

At this time the required tables are statically held within this class. You can however override these tables by specifying the them within the Map metaData passed to the handleRequest(Map metaData) method of this class.

The implementation itself is "in memory". This means the data is processed, held in memory and then output to the neccessary file(s). This approach was taken at this time as the underlying amount of information held for a test instance is not particularly large. In the future, should this change, then the implementation will need to be addapted accordingly.

Author:
Trevor Hinson
